FT  14 MAY 94 / Finance and the Family: Fidelity's cash withdrawal card - At
a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fidelity is adding a cash withdrawal card to its cash unit trust, which
invests in the money markets where banks and other financial institutions
lend and borrow. The card is provided by Clydesdale bank and can be used in
Midland, NatWest, TSB and Link cash withdrawal machines. It allows daily
withdrawals of up to Pounds 200 with no minimum. The card is only available
to those with Pounds 5,000 or more invested in the fund. The initial charge
of Pounds 5 is being waived until May 31.
