<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 94 / International Company News: Austrian privatisation terms set
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK BLUM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   VIENNA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The flotation next week of 51 per cent of VA-Techonologie, Austria's largest
engineering group, is expected to raise Sch6.9bn (Dollars 585m), almost
Sch2bn more than anticipated when the company's privatisation was announced
last November.
Following strong interest from international institutional investors in
Europe and the US, the 7.65m shares on offer have been priced at Sch900 per
share - at the upper end of initial valuations. This would value the company
at Sch13.5bn. 'Demand has been consistently strong across all markets,' the
company said.
VA-Tech's privatisation - the largest Austrian flotation - is part of a
government programme to cut the state's role in industry which it hopes will
raise about Sch20bn over the next 18 months.
The company is owned 75 per cent by OIAG, the Austrian state holding company
for the nationalised industries, and it has a 25 per cent cross shareholding
with VA-Stahl, the steel group which is being restructured to prepare it for
privatisation by 1996.
The flotation on the Vienna stock exchange is set to start on Monday and run
all of next week, but it is expected to close early due to high demand.
</TEXT>
