<TEXT>
Appleby Westward, the USM-traded grocery distributor, saw profits before tax
drop from Pounds 1.28m to just Pounds 221,000 over the 12 months to February
28.
The outcome took in some Pounds 205,000 of non-recurring costs and Pounds
371,000 in sub-contract commissions associated with the agreement last year
with Watson &amp; Philip.
