CDollars 210m special gain on the sale of John Labatt shares. Excluding
special gains, the 1993 quarter loss was CDollars 73m.
Brascan said the gains came mostly from the resource units. Pulp and base
metals prices rose significantly.
The group plans expansion to offset last year's disposal of its main
holdings in MacMillan Bloedel and Labatt. It continues to control Noranda,
Canada's biggest resource group.
