<HEADLINE>
FT  13 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Shaftesbury buoyed by interest cut
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shaftesbury, the property investment company, reported pre-tax profits
sharply higher at Pounds 1.28m for the six months to March 31, against
Pounds 344,000. The main factor was a Pounds 720,000 fall in net interest
charges to Pounds 1.4m.
Earnings per share benefited from a tax refund of Pounds 427,000, coming out
at 3.5p (1.2p). There is no interim dividend, but the capital reduction
during the period will enable a final payment to be recommended.
Sales of properties were lower at Pounds 800,000 (Pounds 1.97m) as turnover
fell to Pounds 4.13m (Pounds 5.22m).
